snippet.textDisplay: <3

Seeing murdoc being left out here and going back to humility, it makes me have a new interpretation of the song, what if 2d was singing about how he thought he needed Murdock and ponders if bringing him back to the band, to their "friendship" would work out. There are some verses that points to that

"I'm the lonely twin, the left hand
Reset myself and get back on track
I don't want this isolation
See the state I'm in now?

Callin' the hunter with a rifle"

Here he's taking about how he thinks his success and wellbeing are due to Murdock leadership, but at the end, he knows that Murdock is a bad mate to have around.

"If I pick it up when I know that it's broken
Do I put it back?"

This is him pondering if he should give a chance to Murdock after all his bullshit, even though he knows Murdock is a dick by nature.

After all that we see Murdock here, all by himself, 2-d made a choice, he will be the leader of his own life, he will not follow Murdock anymore.

Oh, and did you notice that his eyes are white just like when he was happy and confident in humility? Good for him.

snippet.textDisplay:
I completely relate to Murdoc.

On the outside, I'm clearly troubled and some even find me repulsive. I enjoy creating art and helping my friends. Keeping my friends together, helping them, and creating with them gave me so much to look forward to in my life.

When I'm alone I can't help but dread everyday I live because it feels like torment. I've never really been able to take care of myself but I'm still trying to learn. I can feel myself falling apart physically these days, which makes me even scarier to be around. I remember friends I would have given my life for, but they all eventually moved on without me, because I began showing more severe signs of mental illness. Not only was I more difficult to be around and deal with, but the shining qualities and talents I had to provide as a friend became worthless to the world when I started to become dysfunctional.

Some took a lot of me with them. Some weren't even my friends in the first place. But because of my mental illness, I find myself bouncing between fearing being alone, and becoming a recluse when people are around.

These days I cry myself to sleep most nights thinking about all the people that left. I wonder if they would still be around if I was healthier, easier, and happier. I can't help but feel completely worthless. It's always easier to toss me away and forget about me, rather than just stick around for brighter times. The silence is deafening.
I feel sad for Murdoc, just as I do myself. Being abandoned and dealing with the crippling growing pains of being alone, is something I don't think I can ever face with confidence.

When 2D said "Try to hold on to you" I didn't think about all the dead friends I wanted to keep.

I thought about the grip I must keep on myself.
